# Pre-cutover backups written by `task migrate:vbrief` (#497, #506 D7).
# Operators who want these versioned can delete these lines or override per-file.
*.premigrate.*
vbrief/*.premigrate.*

# Migration backups (created by `task migrate:vbrief`) -- do NOT commit.
# Post-commit, pre-migration state is recoverable via git history; see
# deft/main.md § Safety flags for the post-commit recovery path.
*.premigrate.md
*.premigrate.vbrief.json

# Local triage / refinement issue cache (#845 Story 1). Sidecar mirror of
# `gh issue list` populated by `task triage:cache`; never versioned. See
# scripts/triage_cache.py for the layout (.deft-cache/issues/<owner>-<repo>/).
.deft-cache/

# vbrief/.eval/ tracking governance (#1144, N4 of #1119).
# Hybrid policy from the Current Shape comment on #1144:
#   - candidates.jsonl       -> gitignored (operator-private triage decisions;
#                               re-derive via `task triage:bootstrap` on a
#                               fresh clone). #845 Story 2 + #915.
#   - summary-history.jsonl  -> gitignored (operator-private observability;
#                               not load-bearing for any decision).
#   - scope-lifecycle.jsonl  -> gitignored (operator-private scope-lifecycle
#                               audit decisions; D1 / #1121). Per-operator
#                               demote stream; sharing would conflate
#                               operators' demote timing across the team.
#   - decompositions/        -> gitignored (temporary decomposition proposal
#                               drafts; generated child story vBRIEFs live in
#                               lifecycle folders via task scope:decompose).
#   - slices.jsonl           -> TRACKED (team-shared cohort records produced
#                               by slicing skills; see #1132 / D13).
#   - doctor-state.json      -> gitignored (operator-private doctor throttle
#                               state; persisted by `run doctor` /
#                               `task doctor` per #1308 to gate the 24h/4h
#                               re-probe window. Local to each clone; never
#                               committed).
# See vbrief/.eval/README.md for the full policy + merge=union rebase note.
vbrief/.eval/candidates.jsonl
vbrief/.eval/summary-history.jsonl
vbrief/.eval/scope-lifecycle.jsonl
vbrief/.eval/decompositions/
vbrief/.eval/doctor-state.json
vbrief/.eval/*.lock

# N6 (#1146) triage:smoketest assert log -- runtime artefact, never committed.
# The fixture itself (tests/fixtures/triage_smoketest/{issues.json,
# PROJECT-DEFINITION.vbrief.json, vbrief/, README.md}) IS committed; only the
# per-run last_run.json output is gitignored.
tests/fixtures/triage_smoketest/last_run.json

# Monitor scratch (poller scripts, banner-edit helpers, etc.)
.swarm/

# Scratch automation + issue/PR bodies in history/ (WD AI guideline: "prior tasks -> history/").
# These accumulate as one-off helpers per session; never versioned.
history/_*
history/issue-*
history/*.json
history/post-issue.py

# One-off operator scripts left at root from prior sessions -- move to history/ or delete.
poll-fetch.ps1
vbrief/PROJECT-DEFINITION.vbrief.json.lock

# Per-session scratch root files left by orchestrator/swarm handoffs --
# move to history/ or delete; never committed.
.deft-scratch/
docs/incidents/
handoff-*.md
epic_full_body.md
swarm_grok_issue.md
